\begin_layout Subsection
Feature Selection Methodology
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Feature selection is a critical step in developing accurate and interpretable machine learning (ML) models for Parkinson’s disease (PD) detection.
 In this study,
 a multi-method scoring approach was applied to identify the most informative features that differentiate between pre-medication and post-medication states.
 Instead of relying on a single method,
 three complementary techniques were employed,
 and their outputs were combined into a composite score.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Multi-Method Scoring Approach
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For each feature,
 three independent scores were calculated:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Statistical Significance (Paired T-Test):
 A paired T-Test was performed between pre- and post-medication measurements.
 The score was defined as:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\mbox{score}_{T_{\mbox{test}}}=-\log_{10}\left(p_{\mbox{value}}+\epsilon\right)\label{eq:ttest}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\series bold
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon$
\end_inset

 prevents 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

 zero
\series default
 
\series bold
(DEN BGAZEI NOIMA!!!)
\series default
.
 A lower 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{\mbox{value}}$
\end_inset

 corresponds to a higher score,
 indicating stronger statistical significance 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "ttest"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Model-Based Importance
\series default
 (
\series bold
Random Fores
\series default
t):
 A Random Forest classifier was trained,
 and feature importance was derived from the mean decrease in Gini impurity across all trees in the ensemble 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "patel"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 The final outcome here is the 
\begin_inset Formula $\mbox{score}_{RF}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Variance Contribution
\series default
 (
\series bold
PCA
\series default
):
 Principal Component Analysis (PCA) was applied,
 and the importance of each feature was computed as the sum of the absolute loadings across all principal components,
 reflecting its overall contribution to data variance 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Guyon"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 The outcome of this method is 
\begin_inset Formula $\mbox{score}_{\mbox{PCA}}.$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Composite Score Calculation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All three scores were normalized to the 
\begin_inset Formula $[0,1]$
\end_inset

 range.
 A final composite score was then computed as a weighted average:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\mbox{Composite Score}=\mbox{0.4\ensuremath{\times}score}_{T_{\mbox{test}}}+0.3\times\mbox{score}_{RF}+0.3\times\mbox{score}_{\mbox{PCA}}\label{eq:composite}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

This weighting scheme prioritizes statistical significance while also incorporating insights from model-based learning and variance-based analysis.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Selection of best features
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Features were ranked according to their composite score,
 and the top-performing ones were selected for subsequent model development.
 Representative high-ranking features includes:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
RMSSD from the gyroscope during Exercise 2 (score:
 0.663),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Lyapunov Exponent (score:
 0.644),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Higuchi Fractal Dimension (score:
 0.612).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These selected features served as the foundation for later predictive modeling and analysis,
 aiming to capture the most relevant motor signal characteristics associated with PD symptoms 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "goetz,chen"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 In Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Top-20-features"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 the top 20 features are presented.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float table
placement H
alignment document
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Top 20 features scored
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "tab:Top-20-features"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

