\begin_layout Standard
In the experimental tables the following notation is used:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The column DATASET represents the used dataset.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The column RBF stands for the application of an RBF neural network 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "rbf1,rbf2"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 with 10 processing nodes on the corresponding dataset.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The column GEN represents the application of a genetic algorithm 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "geneticnn"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 on the training process of a neural network with 10 processing nodes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The column PCA stands for the application of the PCA method 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "nnpca1,nnpca2,nnpca3"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 to construct two artificial features from the original ones.
 Afterwards,
 a neural network with 10 processing nodes trained using the BFGS method is applied on the new datasets.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The column NNC stands for the application of a neural network constructed with Grammatical Evolution 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "nnc"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 on the corresponding dataset.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The column GENCLASS represents the usage of a method that constructs classification rules using Grammatical Evolution 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "genclass"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The column FC2 is used to represent the application of a genetic algorithm to train a neural network on the dataset produced by the construction of two artificial features using the feature construction method.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The column FC3 is used to represent the application of a genetic algorithm to train a neural network on the dataset produced by the construction of three artificial features using the feature construction method.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The column FC4 is used to represent the application of a genetic algorithm to train a neural network on the dataset produced by the construction of four artificial features using the feature construction method.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The row AVERAGE represents the average classification error for all datasets and the corresponding method.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float table
placement H
alignment document
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
